# Knowledge Extraction

Extraction should happen in multiple stages.

Never ask one LLM to do everything.

Preferred pipeline

Parser

↓

Entity Extraction

↓

Vocabulary Extraction

↓

Theme Classification

↓

Human Experience Classification

↓

Symbol Extraction

↓

Concept Extraction

↓

Commentary Generation

↓

Human Review

Each stage should produce structured JSON.

---

# Human Review

AI proposes.

Curator approves.

The curator UI should allow

Approve

Reject

Merge

Split

Rename

Create New

Every approved entity becomes canonical.

Future ingestion should reuse canonical entities instead of inventing new ones.

---

# Canonical Registry

Maintain a canonical registry for

Themes

Human Experiences

Symbols

Concepts

Literary Devices

AI should always attempt to map to an existing entity before proposing a new one.

This prevents ontology fragmentation.

