# Reader Experience

Users should explore literature through

Poets

Themes

Symbols

Concepts

Human Experiences

Commentaries

Lectures

Not merely through documents.

The reader should be able to ask

"I feel lonely after success."

and discover

Poems

Commentaries

Themes

Symbols

Lectures

rather than keyword matches.

---

# Curator Experience

Separate the Curator application from the Reader application.

Curator responsibilities

Review AI suggestions

Merge ontology

Approve entities

Review commentaries

Review lectures

Manage canonical registry

Reader responsibilities

Read

Search

Explore

Discover

Bookmark

Reflect

---

# Multi-language Strategy

Language should be metadata.

The ontology should remain language independent.

Adding Persian, Arabic or English should require only

New Parser

New Tokenizer

New Vocabulary Dataset

The remainder of the architecture should remain unchanged.

---

# Scalability Principles

Design for

20 million literary units

Optimize for

2,000 literary units

The architecture should never require redesign when the corpus grows.

Only infrastructure should scale.

---

# Long-term Vision

Ma'na is building

"A map of human experience through literature."

The objective is not to explain poems.

The objective is to reveal the relationships between ideas, symbols, themes and experiences across civilizations.

Poems are the entry point.

Meaning is the destination.